==English==
===Etymology===
from Latin '''defunctus''', perfect participle of '''defungi''', ''to finish''
===Adjective===
'''defunct'''
#[[deceased]]
#no longer in use, [[inactive]]
#(computers) a [[process]] that has [[terminated]] but is still shown in the list of processes because child processes created by it are still [[running]].  See also [[zombie]].
#(business) a company that has stopped working, shut down, or dissolved.

